WEBVTT

01:40.470 --> 01:45.930
[Speed and Love]

01:46.229 --> 01:48.830
[Episode 5]

01:52.950 --> 01:53.910
Brandy!

01:55.860 --> 01:57.140
Brandy, are you here?

01:58.420 --> 01:59.259
Brandy!

01:59.420 --> 02:00.670
Zhang, Zhang...

02:00.860 --> 02:01.670
Well,

02:01.830 --> 02:03.780
B-Brandy went to the auto parts market.

02:03.780 --> 02:05.060
If you n-need anything,

02:05.060 --> 02:05.970
just feel free to tell me.

02:05.970 --> 02:06.700
Have a smoke.

02:08.470 --> 02:09.539
Who are they?

02:09.710 --> 02:11.150
Who do you think you are?

02:12.750 --> 02:13.750
Behave yourself.

02:13.820 --> 02:14.660
I've seen

02:14.900 --> 02:16.640
-that yellow-haired man at the boxing gym.
-Brandy!

02:16.640 --> 02:17.570
-That's him.
-Come out!

02:17.570 --> 02:19.500
-He Zhang from Wanji Garage.
-Come out and have fun!

02:19.500 --> 02:20.340
Brandy!

02:20.470 --> 02:21.470
What do they want to do?

02:21.470 --> 02:24.120
Brandy used to work at Wanji Garage
for a few years.

02:24.120 --> 02:26.050
After he started his own business,

02:26.100 --> 02:28.430
that man's been coming here to harass him.

02:30.310 --> 02:31.150
Stay here.

02:35.430 --> 02:36.560
Well, hello, Zhang.

02:37.590 --> 02:38.660
Long time no see.

02:40.820 --> 02:42.620
But what's going on now?

02:43.270 --> 02:45.150
Taking advantage while the owner is away

02:45.150 --> 02:47.340
and causing trouble, what does that prove?

02:47.340 --> 02:49.100
Those who know you might think
you're just fooling around.

02:49.100 --> 02:50.060
But others

02:51.030 --> 02:54.160
might think you're cowards
taking advantage of people.

02:54.470 --> 02:56.020
We all work and live in this area.

02:56.020 --> 02:58.220
It'll be embarrassing if word gets out.

02:58.750 --> 03:00.280
It's none of your business.

03:00.710 --> 03:01.430
Get lost.

03:02.660 --> 03:04.500
Go pet your cat somewhere else.

03:04.780 --> 03:06.910
Were it not for the sake of your father,

03:07.340 --> 03:09.030
I'd mess with you, too.

03:10.220 --> 03:12.210
Your lackeys with their barking habits

03:12.210 --> 03:13.600
haven't changed a bit.

03:16.220 --> 03:17.780
If you're here today for chitchat,

03:17.780 --> 03:18.990
I'm totally up for that.

03:18.990 --> 03:20.340
But tell your men

03:20.820 --> 03:22.220
to stop running their mouths

03:22.220 --> 03:23.680
and bringing up my father.

03:23.910 --> 03:25.960
He gambles and parties like you guys,

03:25.960 --> 03:27.690
but I'm a law-abiding citizen.

03:27.990 --> 03:29.750
Cutting me some slack for his sake is

03:29.750 --> 03:31.210
completely unnecessary.

03:34.100 --> 03:35.430
What are you looking at?

03:39.390 --> 03:40.520
You fix cars, right?

03:41.500 --> 03:42.610
I'll fix them for you!

03:42.610 --> 03:43.370
Your hands!

03:47.380 --> 03:48.100
Hands off.

03:48.280 --> 03:48.960
What?

03:49.450 --> 03:50.980
Is this your family's shop?

03:51.380 --> 03:52.440
You got that right.

03:59.390 --> 03:59.790
I...

03:59.820 --> 04:00.700
What?

04:01.270 --> 04:03.280
So Wanji Garage will start
hitting women now?

04:03.280 --> 04:04.340
If you have any problem, come at me.

04:04.340 --> 04:05.270
Come at me.

04:07.270 --> 04:07.770
Move aside.

04:07.770 --> 04:08.490
No!

04:09.220 --> 04:10.150
I'm livestreaming.

04:10.150 --> 04:10.940
-It's live.
-Put your phone away!

04:10.940 --> 04:11.620
Put it away.

04:11.710 --> 04:13.060
-It's live!
-Who are you pointing at? -Move!

04:13.060 --> 04:14.590
-Put your phone away.
-It's live!

04:14.590 --> 04:16.829
It's live! I'm livestreaming! It's live...

04:16.829 --> 04:17.560
Give it to me.

04:17.950 --> 04:18.709
Let go of me.

04:18.730 --> 04:19.459
Give me that.

04:30.280 --> 04:32.380
You tried to smash my car
and mess with my people.

04:32.380 --> 04:33.100
Do you want to die?

04:33.100 --> 04:33.909
What?

04:34.150 --> 04:35.150
Want to try me?

05:20.320 --> 05:21.650
I'm calling the police.

05:29.540 --> 05:30.630
This isn't over.

05:31.710 --> 05:32.710
I'll wait and see.

05:39.980 --> 05:40.650
Let's go!

05:46.710 --> 05:47.770
Did that scare you?

05:48.100 --> 05:48.909
You're hurt.

05:48.950 --> 05:49.750
It's nothing.

05:52.270 --> 05:53.030
Are you okay?

06:04.710 --> 06:05.510
What's wrong?

06:05.560 --> 06:07.690
Why didn't you call the police before?

06:10.070 --> 06:11.300
You can consider it

06:11.470 --> 06:13.070
an unspoken rule of the game.

06:13.340 --> 06:15.340
As long as no one's life is in danger,

06:15.390 --> 06:16.490
even if the police come,

06:16.490 --> 06:18.090
there isn't much they can do.

06:18.150 --> 06:19.350
How can they mediate?

06:19.740 --> 06:20.980
They settle it this time,

06:20.980 --> 06:23.860
and we call them again next time
when there's trouble.

06:23.860 --> 06:25.860
We can't waste their time like that.

06:27.180 --> 06:28.740
But judging from the way they acted,

06:28.740 --> 06:30.590
they clearly came to cause trouble.

06:30.590 --> 06:32.650
And you couldn't beat them in a fight.

06:34.180 --> 06:34.950
Have a seat.

06:38.540 --> 06:40.000
Let me tell you something.

06:40.300 --> 06:41.540
Brandy might seem

06:41.740 --> 06:43.880
to always bury himself in work every day,

06:43.880 --> 06:46.740
but you haven't seen him
back in Shakun High School.

06:47.270 --> 06:48.300
Back then...

06:51.350 --> 06:55.030
You have no idea what he used to be like
when he was still

06:55.070 --> 06:55.990
called Touqi.

06:56.270 --> 06:57.560
Not to mention these 3 guys today,

06:57.560 --> 07:00.910
he could even handle a dozen of them
without breaking a sweat.

07:00.910 --> 07:03.640
He had nothing to lose,
but others wanted to live.

07:03.740 --> 07:05.150
Actually, with his build now,

07:05.150 --> 07:06.940
he could still knock down 10 guys.

07:06.940 --> 07:09.400
It just depends
on whether he wants to fight.

07:09.420 --> 07:11.660
When people from Wanji Garage
came to cause trouble before,

07:11.660 --> 07:12.830
Brandy didn't even fight back.

07:12.830 --> 07:14.560
He just somehow sent them away.

07:15.220 --> 07:16.470
But today,

07:19.570 --> 07:21.300
it was probably because of you.

07:23.910 --> 07:25.740
Actually, every time
those Wanji Garage guys come,

07:25.740 --> 07:27.630
they're not really here to wreak havoc.

07:27.630 --> 07:29.390
They just come to cause some small trouble

07:29.390 --> 07:31.250
and mess with Brandy's business.

07:31.470 --> 07:32.740
Touqi?

07:36.740 --> 07:38.100
Is Touqi Jin Zhao?

07:38.220 --> 07:39.590
Why was he called Touqi?

07:41.830 --> 07:43.470
You are so sharp
at spotting the key points.

07:43.470 --> 07:44.390
I never mentioned this.

07:44.390 --> 07:45.120
I know nothing about it.

07:45.120 --> 07:46.780
Don't tell him I told you that.

07:55.940 --> 07:58.220
So why does Wanji Garage
have it in for Jin Zhao?

07:58.220 --> 07:59.420
Do they have a grudge?

07:59.980 --> 08:02.510
Brandy worked
at Wanji Garage for many years

08:02.710 --> 08:04.070
and eventually made it to senior mechanic,

08:04.070 --> 08:06.070
in charge of quite a few apprentices.

08:06.070 --> 08:07.910
But later, because of some issues,

08:07.910 --> 08:09.620
he decided to leave Wanji Garage.

08:09.620 --> 08:11.210
Iron Cock left with Brandy.

08:11.510 --> 08:12.980
After they both left,

08:13.360 --> 08:15.030
a host of other junior mechanics

08:15.030 --> 08:16.710
either went to other shops
or quit altogether.

08:16.710 --> 08:18.710
It caused a big blow to Wanji Garage.

08:18.710 --> 08:19.850
Later, the two of them opened this shop,

08:19.850 --> 08:21.710
and many old clients followed them here.

08:21.710 --> 08:22.850
If you were one of Wanji Garage,

08:22.850 --> 08:24.450
would you let him off easily?

08:24.630 --> 08:26.490
After all, when Brandy was there,

08:26.830 --> 08:27.660
Wanji Garage's business was

08:27.660 --> 08:28.860
really thriving.

08:51.850 --> 08:52.820
Is Jin Zhao

08:54.230 --> 08:56.490
involved in some dangerous activities?

08:57.520 --> 08:58.550
What do you mean?

08:59.110 --> 09:00.870
Things that threaten his life.

09:04.820 --> 09:06.150
Underground fighting?

09:06.780 --> 09:07.780
And street racing

09:09.360 --> 09:10.890
with a dangerous crowd.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.820
I think you know a bit too much.

09:15.370 --> 09:16.910
What other details do you know?

09:16.910 --> 09:17.270
I don't know.

09:17.270 --> 09:17.780
-I really have no idea.
-Tell me.

09:17.780 --> 09:18.460
I know nothing!

09:18.460 --> 09:20.520
Stop asking me. I know nothing at all!

09:21.380 --> 09:22.500
So loud.

09:25.910 --> 09:27.300
If Sanlai doesn't want to talk about it,

09:27.300 --> 09:28.430
I can't force him to.

09:29.940 --> 09:31.510
Shakun High School.

09:31.940 --> 09:32.990
Touqi.

09:34.180 --> 09:35.780
I must get to the bottom of it.

09:36.750 --> 09:37.680
Brandy, Brandy.

09:38.270 --> 09:38.940
Come give me a hand.

09:38.940 --> 09:40.050
Let's lift this rack first.

09:40.050 --> 09:41.120
-Master.
-Let me help.

09:41.120 --> 09:41.980
Please help us.

09:47.120 --> 09:48.570
Why is this so heavy?

09:49.580 --> 09:50.530
If you were any stronger,

09:50.530 --> 09:51.930
you could move the Earth.

09:52.370 --> 09:54.500
Don't get yourself dirty. Step aside.

09:55.930 --> 09:58.460
Let's not
talk about moving the Earth for now.

09:59.210 --> 09:59.930
Pardon?

10:00.330 --> 10:02.640
I said you're underestimating me.

10:04.330 --> 10:05.860
Come on. Put it down slowly.

10:25.600 --> 10:26.760
I wouldn't dare underestimate you.

10:26.760 --> 10:27.600
Come with me.

10:33.640 --> 10:35.090
I have an important task for you.

10:35.090 --> 10:36.150
Pick up the screws.

10:42.870 --> 10:43.440
Come on.

10:43.600 --> 10:45.000
Let's lift this first.

11:15.060 --> 11:16.370
One, two, three, up!

12:04.200 --> 12:04.840
Mu,

12:05.090 --> 12:06.350
they need to be sorted.

12:14.910 --> 12:15.820
Yang,

12:16.160 --> 12:17.680
does he look down on me?

12:18.300 --> 12:19.150
No, not at all.

12:19.420 --> 12:21.180
Picking up screws is quite a hard job.

12:21.180 --> 12:22.700
Like me, I have
no fingerprints on my hands.

12:22.700 --> 12:24.100
I just can't pick them up.

13:05.750 --> 13:07.950
A Wankel engine in a pickup for home use.

13:10.040 --> 13:10.920
Interesting.

13:13.660 --> 13:15.150
Send me this address.

13:18.920 --> 13:23.640
[Pet Home]

14:00.950 --> 14:01.980
Hello.

14:05.020 --> 14:05.940
Can I help you?

14:06.750 --> 14:08.010
You can speak Chinese.

14:08.940 --> 14:09.940
Speak Chinese?

14:10.430 --> 14:11.890
I thought you were a local.

14:11.990 --> 14:13.590
I am indeed a local.

14:14.390 --> 14:16.060
Your Chinese is pretty good then.

14:16.060 --> 14:17.920
Tell me what you would like to see.

14:17.940 --> 14:18.660
Cars.

14:18.810 --> 14:19.640
Cars?

14:21.270 --> 14:22.200
Perfect timing.

14:22.210 --> 14:22.850
We just

14:23.170 --> 14:24.230
got two new models.

14:24.420 --> 14:25.940
One is a convertible like this.

14:25.940 --> 14:27.600
This one comes with a mesh bag.

14:27.660 --> 14:29.180
But we only have these two colors.

14:29.180 --> 14:30.380
Which one do you want?

14:30.910 --> 14:32.710
Racing cars for mountain roads.

14:32.750 --> 14:34.030
R-Racing cars?

14:34.580 --> 14:36.160
We don't have racing cars for pets here.

14:36.160 --> 14:37.160
Last Saturday,

14:37.580 --> 14:39.510
the 15th, at 11 o'clock at night,

14:39.860 --> 14:40.730
where were you?

14:43.030 --> 14:44.420
Last Saturday?

14:44.820 --> 14:46.110
At night?

14:46.650 --> 14:49.540
-Did Jin Zhao mess with anyone again?
-The CCTV caught

14:49.540 --> 14:51.680
a black RX7.

14:52.580 --> 14:53.350
It wasn't me.

14:54.420 --> 14:55.150
Do you have any evidence?

14:55.150 --> 14:56.750
Was my face caught on camera?

14:59.120 --> 15:01.150
Actually, we didn't get a clear face shot.

15:01.150 --> 15:02.820
No face shot means no evidence.

15:02.820 --> 15:03.960
Don't falsely accuse the innocent.

15:03.960 --> 15:05.110
We just have these two cars
for you to buy.

15:05.110 --> 15:05.870
If you don't want any,

15:05.870 --> 15:08.000
see the entrance there? You can leave.

15:15.660 --> 15:18.210
Is that car at the entrance yours?

15:19.540 --> 15:20.740
What's your problem?

15:23.270 --> 15:25.460
A pickup truck specifically used
by a pet shop

15:25.460 --> 15:26.660
to transport animals

15:26.840 --> 15:29.040
with 1,000 HP, 2,000 torque,

15:29.940 --> 15:31.870
mounted with a Wankel engine,

15:32.020 --> 15:35.270
can run even faster
than supercars on the track.

15:40.620 --> 15:42.020
1,000 HP, 2,000 torque,

15:42.230 --> 15:43.430
with a Wankel engine.

15:44.360 --> 15:45.290
What do you mean?

15:47.540 --> 15:50.030
It can run even faster
than supercars on the track.

15:50.030 --> 15:52.290
He said the exact same thing Brandy said.

15:54.570 --> 15:56.610
You've got good taste, bro.

15:57.780 --> 15:58.540
That car is

15:59.060 --> 15:59.860
indeed mine.

16:00.540 --> 16:01.630
Why didn't you

16:01.810 --> 16:04.670
turn on your headlights
before the bend that night?

16:04.850 --> 16:08.180
Brandy was caught driving at night
with the headlights off?

16:10.630 --> 16:13.430
Have you heard
of the Racing Legend of Mount Akina?

16:14.180 --> 16:15.810
About the Japanese mountain rally racing?

16:15.810 --> 16:17.090
I'm not boasting.

16:17.700 --> 16:20.180
I'm the Racing Legend of Chinatown.

16:20.710 --> 16:21.730
If you don't mind,

16:21.800 --> 16:23.050
just call me Lord Sanlai

16:23.050 --> 16:24.400
like everyone else.

16:30.880 --> 16:32.480
Was it really you that night?

16:37.660 --> 16:38.540
Bro,

16:39.460 --> 16:41.390
you're asking too many questions.

16:42.030 --> 16:42.990
But that's okay.

16:43.390 --> 16:44.030
Here,

16:45.230 --> 16:46.150
a gold card for 1 question

16:46.150 --> 16:47.100
and a platinum card for 3.

16:47.100 --> 16:47.960
Take your pick.

16:51.850 --> 16:52.760
Platinum card.

16:54.230 --> 16:55.060
Very classy.

16:55.350 --> 16:57.750
Ask whatever you want.
I'll go register it.

17:01.500 --> 17:02.340
Excuse me.

17:03.260 --> 17:06.020
When will this bird come down?

17:07.599 --> 17:10.050
That's not a bird. That's my little sun.

17:11.910 --> 17:12.910
Excuse me.

17:13.210 --> 17:15.500
When will your two little suns

17:15.990 --> 17:18.579
ever come down?

17:18.599 --> 17:20.050
They quite like you.

17:20.650 --> 17:21.710
My little suns

17:21.740 --> 17:23.310
prefer classy people.

17:23.579 --> 17:24.910
They'll come down soon.

17:26.579 --> 17:27.990
Do you love me that much?

17:29.220 --> 17:30.200
Excuse me.

17:30.390 --> 17:32.660
When will they come down?

17:32.910 --> 17:33.630
Soon.

17:34.460 --> 17:35.190
Here you are.

17:35.560 --> 17:36.290
Your card.

17:37.660 --> 17:38.420
Go away now.

17:39.670 --> 17:40.210
Go.

17:43.610 --> 17:44.500
Then...

17:45.740 --> 17:46.550
This...

17:48.950 --> 17:51.150
You've asked three questions already.

17:51.760 --> 17:53.780
I need you to answer my question.

17:53.870 --> 17:55.550
I can answer your question.

17:56.330 --> 17:58.090
But about the money...

17:58.630 --> 17:59.870
Money is no problem.

18:00.100 --> 18:01.900
You should have said it earlier.

18:02.150 --> 18:02.740
Here.

18:02.980 --> 18:05.110
Supreme VIP membership, 88888.

18:05.220 --> 18:06.610
24-hour service anytime.

18:06.610 --> 18:08.140
Ask any questions you want.

18:12.150 --> 18:13.390
What's your name?

18:18.390 --> 18:19.150
DRUNK?

18:19.980 --> 18:20.660
Lin Sui?

18:20.680 --> 18:21.810
You know each other?

18:22.990 --> 18:23.790
No.

18:24.550 --> 18:25.150
We've met.

18:25.500 --> 18:26.260
This guy

18:26.290 --> 18:27.950
just came to my shop to find me.

18:28.180 --> 18:28.870
To buy a cat?

18:28.960 --> 18:31.290
He came asking about a car,
about your car.

18:31.390 --> 18:33.150
He saw you last Saturday night.

18:33.270 --> 18:34.030
He also showed me

18:34.030 --> 18:36.150
a screenshot of the surveillance footage.

18:36.150 --> 18:36.980
It didn't capture your face,

18:36.980 --> 18:38.380
but it was obviously you.

18:40.940 --> 18:41.630
And then?

18:41.780 --> 18:44.130
You tricked him into getting a membership?

18:44.130 --> 18:45.520
Mind your words.

18:45.550 --> 18:47.260
What do you mean by "tricked"?

18:47.790 --> 18:50.200
Do you know how rare it is
to run into such an easy mark?

18:50.200 --> 18:51.260
It's extremely...

18:52.420 --> 18:53.260
But anyway,

18:53.490 --> 18:54.460
I beat around the bush

18:54.460 --> 18:55.460
concerning all the questions

18:55.460 --> 18:56.570
he asked about your personal info

18:56.570 --> 18:57.880
and didn't say a word.

18:58.420 --> 18:59.350
Am I loyal enough?

18:59.350 --> 19:00.220
If you could be this tough

19:00.220 --> 19:01.670
when dealing with Wan Qing,

19:01.670 --> 19:03.200
it'd spare me much trouble.

19:04.700 --> 19:05.910
W-Well, about that woman,

19:05.910 --> 19:07.640
that's going to cost you extra.

19:07.940 --> 19:09.310
Anyway, this guy set an appointment

19:09.310 --> 19:10.830
with me for next Saturday.

19:11.020 --> 19:11.690
And where?

19:12.550 --> 19:13.520
He said I'd know.

19:17.310 --> 19:18.170
Did you say yes?

19:18.460 --> 19:20.310
I had no reason to turn him down!

19:20.660 --> 19:22.190
With this kind of rich fool,

19:22.420 --> 19:23.830
I'd like to meet him again

19:23.830 --> 19:25.360
and maybe find some new way

19:25.390 --> 19:26.320
to make a profit.

19:26.890 --> 19:27.910
But I really don't know the location.

19:27.910 --> 19:28.910
He didn't tell me.

19:28.940 --> 19:30.670
He's challenging you to a race.

19:31.350 --> 19:32.210
The location is

19:32.490 --> 19:33.570
at Doi Inthanon.

19:35.620 --> 19:36.660
Wait, what on earth

19:36.660 --> 19:37.980
happened that night?

19:39.070 --> 19:40.070
Nothing.

19:40.300 --> 19:41.500
I was just passing by.

19:43.400 --> 19:44.790
Right, he also asked me

19:44.790 --> 19:47.850
why you didn't turn on your headlights
before the bend.

19:48.590 --> 19:49.390
I fell asleep.

19:52.440 --> 19:53.630
With my poor skills,

19:53.660 --> 19:55.120
how can I compete with him?

19:55.170 --> 19:58.500
I'll completely ruin the title
of Lord Sanlai of Chinatown.

20:00.640 --> 20:02.290
Come on. I'll take you somewhere

20:02.290 --> 20:03.750
and teach you some skills.

20:04.550 --> 20:06.740
Really? Will it work?

20:14.790 --> 20:16.070
So this is the cat

20:16.110 --> 20:17.990
in the photo that easy mark showed me.

20:17.990 --> 20:19.850
So cool. I'll train with this one.

20:19.980 --> 20:21.730
This car isn't a good fit for you.

20:21.730 --> 20:22.570
Why?

20:23.790 --> 20:25.220
Modified cars are usually

20:25.220 --> 20:27.550
divided into Japanese and German styles.

20:27.550 --> 20:29.050
Japanese style pursues extremes,

20:29.050 --> 20:30.660
like madmen with no limits.

20:32.090 --> 20:34.330
This one is a Japanese classic.

20:36.350 --> 20:37.750
What about German style?

20:38.020 --> 20:41.020
German cars can be understood
as straight-A students

20:41.350 --> 20:43.080
who strictly follow the rules.

20:45.110 --> 20:46.510
So what's your style now?

20:47.020 --> 20:49.940
Once a rule-following straight-A student

20:50.060 --> 20:51.500
and now

20:51.870 --> 20:53.500
a madman with no limits?

20:55.250 --> 20:56.310
You could say that.

20:56.770 --> 20:58.100
Let me explain it to you.

20:59.020 --> 21:01.220
Japanese cars are lighter themselves.

21:01.260 --> 21:03.460
To achieve
better handling and stability, they even

21:03.460 --> 21:05.310
try to reduce the weight
as much as possible.

21:05.310 --> 21:06.420
As for German cars,

21:06.420 --> 21:08.160
they're heavier with rigid bodies,

21:08.160 --> 21:09.310
not easily deformed,

21:09.310 --> 21:10.110
with greater inertia,

21:10.110 --> 21:12.110
but they offer stability and comfort.

21:12.110 --> 21:13.110
Some Japanese cars

21:13.110 --> 21:14.870
also install roll bars, strut bars,

21:14.870 --> 21:16.330
and other stuff to achieve

21:16.440 --> 21:17.570
ultimate rigidity.

21:18.420 --> 21:19.630
Come take a look at this.

21:19.630 --> 21:20.630
You said so much,

21:20.710 --> 21:22.440
yet I didn't get a single thing.

21:25.820 --> 21:27.170
Oh, my God!

21:27.870 --> 21:29.940
Isn't this Fujiwara Takumi's AE86?

21:30.500 --> 21:31.390
Let's go with this one.

21:31.390 --> 21:33.390
Sure! It's so cool!

21:38.640 --> 21:39.250
Here.

21:39.650 --> 21:40.310
Put this on.

21:43.030 --> 21:43.750
What?

21:43.980 --> 21:44.830
Does this hat of yours

21:44.830 --> 21:46.760
come with instant driving skills?

21:46.840 --> 21:48.240
Why do I need to wear a hat?

21:51.030 --> 21:52.830
What does this moon symbol mean?

21:55.380 --> 21:56.590
In the name of the moon,

21:56.590 --> 21:57.520
I'll punish you.

22:00.550 --> 22:01.220
Let's go!

22:02.800 --> 22:04.530
Get in! I'll take you for a ride.

22:08.760 --> 22:09.720
Come on! Get in!

22:13.570 --> 22:14.670
I'll teach you some skills

22:14.670 --> 22:16.400
that should be enough to get by.

22:48.110 --> 22:48.940
Hi, gorgeous.

22:49.420 --> 22:51.310
Looking for a spin in the 86?

22:51.310 --> 22:52.890
-Look at this man.
-Is he out of his mind,

22:52.890 --> 22:54.550
wearing sunglasses at night?

23:03.200 --> 23:04.330
Let's go.

23:06.200 --> 23:08.600
Let me take you to a closed road
to practice.

23:20.820 --> 23:22.870
First, I'll teach you
full-throttle shifting.

23:22.870 --> 23:24.130
To accelerate faster,

23:24.220 --> 23:25.940
keep the gas pedal floored the whole time.

23:25.940 --> 23:27.980
You need to shift gears
and release the clutch very quickly.

23:27.980 --> 23:29.840
I'll demonstrate it for you once.

23:58.950 --> 23:59.970
Now let's switch seats.

23:59.970 --> 24:00.700
Give it a try.

24:02.420 --> 24:03.070
Wait,

24:03.420 --> 24:03.980
I haven't even

24:03.980 --> 24:05.380
memorized how you drove!

24:05.830 --> 24:07.350
You drive first.
You're unfamiliar with the pedals.

24:07.350 --> 24:09.150
I'll remind you while you drive.

24:14.080 --> 24:15.320
Step on the clutch,

24:16.630 --> 24:17.690
then the gas pedal.

24:18.460 --> 24:19.190
Shift gears.

24:19.390 --> 24:20.830
Shift gears and release.

24:23.600 --> 24:24.630
What's happening?

24:24.630 --> 24:25.930
Keep the accelerator steady.

24:25.930 --> 24:27.910
Release your left foot directly
and shift gears.

24:27.910 --> 24:28.740
Okay.

24:28.880 --> 24:30.540
I've got it steady. Just wait.

24:31.930 --> 24:33.020
Wait, no, I... How can I...

24:33.020 --> 24:34.410
I can't shift gears right now.

24:34.410 --> 24:35.350
Use your hands and feet together!

24:35.350 --> 24:36.950
I-I just can't do it. I can't.

24:37.020 --> 24:38.040
What should I do? Hurry!

24:38.040 --> 24:38.840
Do it this way.

24:39.020 --> 24:40.150
Follow my commands.

24:40.180 --> 24:42.220
I'll help you shift gears,
and then you release the clutch.

24:42.220 --> 24:42.830
Okay.

24:43.790 --> 24:45.590
Three, two, one.

24:45.850 --> 24:46.530
Go!

24:51.260 --> 24:52.590
I'll shift gears for you one more time.

24:52.590 --> 24:54.110
Three, two, one.

24:57.940 --> 24:59.070
What should I do now?

24:59.420 --> 25:00.820
Hey, you want to take off?

25:00.980 --> 25:03.040
Have some patience with me, will you?

25:19.840 --> 25:20.910
Can't you teach me

25:20.940 --> 25:22.520
the fastest, coolest,

25:22.550 --> 25:24.280
most awesome drift technique?

25:24.550 --> 25:25.280
Get off.

25:41.330 --> 25:43.570
Gotta drift! Drift with style!

26:01.980 --> 26:03.420
That's sick, bro!

26:03.680 --> 26:04.400
Get off now.

26:25.220 --> 26:26.870
Pick what you most want to ask.

26:26.870 --> 26:27.630
True love.

26:27.830 --> 26:28.660
Just help me tell

26:28.660 --> 26:30.120
if I'm his true love or not.

26:30.350 --> 26:32.180
I don't care about all those other women.

26:32.180 --> 26:34.440
I need to know
if I'm the right one for him.

26:38.570 --> 26:39.400
Moon?

26:40.020 --> 26:41.820
What does this moon symbol mean?

26:42.570 --> 26:45.400
If I sleep with him
on the night of the full moon,

26:45.730 --> 26:48.250
we can be together forever and ever?

26:49.530 --> 26:50.330
Qing,

26:50.730 --> 26:52.790
wouldn't that make you a seductress?

26:55.820 --> 26:56.890
What seductress?

26:57.940 --> 26:59.830
Haven't you read martial arts novels?

26:58.270 --> 26:59.650
[Jiang Mu]

27:01.150 --> 27:02.950
Right, what you said makes sense.

27:02.950 --> 27:04.150
It could be like that.

27:04.590 --> 27:06.310
See? I was right.

27:06.350 --> 27:07.350
S-So, Qing,

27:07.710 --> 27:09.390
which martial arts novel is that from?

27:09.390 --> 27:10.390
You illiterate.

27:10.940 --> 27:13.310
Jin Yong's "The Deer and the Cauldron."

27:14.700 --> 27:15.640
I've read that one!

27:15.640 --> 27:17.260
Its protagonist, Wei Xiaobao, has...

27:17.260 --> 27:18.560
He has 7 wives!

27:18.590 --> 27:19.980
Those women are all quite pretty.

27:19.980 --> 27:20.830
Yes, beautiful.

27:20.830 --> 27:21.830
My favorite is...

27:25.570 --> 27:26.570
-Qing.
-Qing.

27:27.590 --> 27:29.470
Wei Xiaobao? 7 wives?

27:29.500 --> 27:30.350
What nonsense is this?

27:30.350 --> 27:33.810
Do you think this is the kind of man
that I, Wan Qing, am looking for?

27:33.810 --> 27:34.500
Say that again!

27:34.500 --> 27:35.410
I... Please stop hitting me, Qing!

27:35.410 --> 27:36.300
It hurts.

27:43.330 --> 27:44.090
Where is she?

27:45.790 --> 27:46.630
She ran away.

27:46.900 --> 27:49.070
S-She just ran away, I think.

27:50.790 --> 27:52.250
The Shakun High School
you asked about yesterday

27:52.250 --> 27:53.580
happens to be my school.

27:53.980 --> 27:55.250
Over there is our playground,

27:55.250 --> 27:57.850
where everyone
has PE classes and activities.

27:58.220 --> 27:59.920
This is our school's classroom building.

27:59.920 --> 28:01.020
And further that way are

28:01.020 --> 28:02.550
our school's dormitories.

28:02.580 --> 28:03.910
Students rest and relax

28:03.910 --> 28:04.790
in that area.

28:05.350 --> 28:06.930
Over there is our school cafeteria.

28:06.930 --> 28:08.530
The food in our cafeteria is so good.

28:08.530 --> 28:09.730
You must give it a try.

28:11.460 --> 28:12.390
This area here is

28:12.390 --> 28:13.910
our school's honor board.

28:14.020 --> 28:14.790
Honor board?

28:14.980 --> 28:16.350
The honor board features

28:16.350 --> 28:17.980
some outstanding senior students,

28:17.980 --> 28:19.630
quiz competition winners,

28:19.700 --> 28:21.700
and sports competition champions.

28:23.850 --> 28:25.180
Are you out of class now?

28:29.010 --> 28:30.680
Jin Zhao in this photo is

28:31.510 --> 28:33.310
exactly how I imagined him.

28:34.610 --> 28:36.170
What exactly happened

28:36.510 --> 28:38.370
that made him give up his studies?

28:42.200 --> 28:42.960
You know him?

28:45.620 --> 28:46.710
It's him?

28:47.870 --> 28:49.910
Jīn Zhao.

28:50.680 --> 28:51.600
Jìn Zhao.

28:52.790 --> 28:54.480
Your names are really interesting.

28:54.480 --> 28:57.320
He's Jīn Zhao, and you're Jiang Mu.

29:09.050 --> 29:10.070
It's these two characters.

29:10.070 --> 29:11.800
Jin Zhao. It's pronounced Jìn.

29:12.200 --> 29:12.960
Mu,

29:13.330 --> 29:15.130
your handwriting is beautiful.

29:15.350 --> 29:16.590
If my mother, who works so hard practicing

29:16.590 --> 29:17.630
Chinese characters, sees this,

29:17.630 --> 29:19.560
she'll surely be so envious of you.

29:21.590 --> 29:23.050
My teacher taught me well.

29:24.950 --> 29:26.320
Look at your names.

29:27.350 --> 29:28.310
One is Zhao,

29:28.660 --> 29:29.630
so he is the sun.

29:30.070 --> 29:30.830
One is Mu,

29:30.980 --> 29:31.980
so you are the moon.

29:31.980 --> 29:33.420
Together,

29:34.700 --> 29:36.560
morning and night, day after day.

29:44.940 --> 29:45.710
Nana.

29:47.040 --> 29:48.630
I want to study here too.

30:03.980 --> 30:06.440
Smoking is bad for your health.
Don't smoke.

30:11.780 --> 30:12.980
Then I'll smoke, too.

30:13.960 --> 30:15.160
Don't be ridiculous.

30:25.640 --> 30:26.700
I forgot to tell you

30:26.940 --> 30:28.240
that I've learned Taekwondo

30:28.240 --> 30:29.970
as a second-degree black belt.

30:34.740 --> 30:35.780
Just fancy moves.

30:36.250 --> 30:37.960
It's enough to deal with you.

30:38.620 --> 30:40.280
I bet you wouldn't hit a woman.

30:46.670 --> 30:48.600
Don't think of me as such a nice guy.

30:50.180 --> 30:51.020
Jin Zhao,

30:51.830 --> 30:53.910
why have you become so bad-tempered?

30:57.990 --> 31:00.050
My temper is actually quite good now.

31:00.420 --> 31:01.620
If it were 2 years ago,

31:02.150 --> 31:04.280
you'd have ended up in the river by now.

31:04.500 --> 31:05.220
Also,

31:07.030 --> 31:08.430
what did you just call me?

31:09.550 --> 31:10.460
Jin Zhao.

31:14.700 --> 31:15.590
Jin Zhao.

31:16.590 --> 31:18.110
Jin Zhao.

31:19.180 --> 31:20.350
Jin Zhao.

31:21.870 --> 31:22.750
I've decided

31:22.880 --> 31:24.680
not to call you brother anymore.

31:24.820 --> 31:27.410
I'll just call you
by your full name, Jin Zhao.

31:39.000 --> 31:40.040
Jiang Mu.

31:40.900 --> 31:42.870
Stop clinging to your brother, Jin Zhao.

31:42.870 --> 31:44.020
I need a partner while I practice driving.

31:44.020 --> 31:44.830
Do me a favor.

31:45.110 --> 31:46.870
Sanlai, why aren't you wearing

31:46.870 --> 31:48.530
your colorful clothes today?

31:48.940 --> 31:50.930
I'm going for a mature, steady look today,

31:50.930 --> 31:53.060
just changing my style occasionally.

31:54.180 --> 31:56.120
What did you just say? Practice driving?

31:56.120 --> 31:56.920
That's right.

31:57.310 --> 31:58.070
Actually, I've always

31:58.070 --> 32:00.400
had a hidden identity I haven't revealed.

32:00.570 --> 32:01.290
What is it?

32:01.830 --> 32:04.350
The Racing Legend of Chinatown, known as

32:04.950 --> 32:06.480
Lord Sanlai of Chinatown.

32:13.860 --> 32:15.100
Racing Legend?

32:16.110 --> 32:18.310
Driving this flashy pink pickup truck?

32:18.370 --> 32:20.060
This isn't flashy pink.

32:20.200 --> 32:21.920
This is Barbie Girl pink.

32:22.130 --> 32:24.190
1,000 HP, 2,000 torque,

32:24.220 --> 32:25.050
with a Wankel engine.

32:25.050 --> 32:26.090
It can run even faster

32:26.090 --> 32:27.690
than supercars on the track.

32:29.420 --> 32:30.750
Where are we going then?

32:30.910 --> 32:32.570
Let's go to the driving range.

32:32.980 --> 32:33.840
Are you coming?

32:38.100 --> 32:40.170
Of course!
Or why would I ask where we're going?

32:40.170 --> 32:41.180
I'll go get something.

32:41.180 --> 32:41.830
Okay.

33:18.080 --> 33:19.110
Where's Sanlai?

33:19.460 --> 33:20.390
In the bathroom.

33:23.350 --> 33:25.150
Then I'll wait for him in the car.

33:27.040 --> 33:28.200
The key is with me.

33:41.290 --> 33:42.350
Give me the car key.

33:42.350 --> 33:43.080
She took it.

33:45.740 --> 33:46.540
What's wrong?

33:46.920 --> 33:47.890
Well,

33:49.350 --> 33:51.430
what's with girls this age nowadays?

33:52.420 --> 33:53.950
She was just clinging to me,

33:54.610 --> 33:56.320
but now she's suddenly avoiding me,

33:56.320 --> 33:58.250
running away faster than a rabbit.

33:58.600 --> 34:01.050
Hey, you're really weird.

34:01.660 --> 34:03.260
When everyone was going through puberty,

34:03.260 --> 34:04.420
you weren't interested in women.

34:04.420 --> 34:06.220
Now you're asking me about this?

34:06.310 --> 34:07.740
What are you talking about?

34:07.740 --> 34:08.710
What did you do to her?

34:08.710 --> 34:09.909
Did you bully her?

34:10.060 --> 34:11.790
What could I possibly do to her?

34:13.870 --> 34:14.909
Let me tell you.

34:15.710 --> 34:17.620
Don't try to guess
what women are thinking.

34:17.620 --> 34:19.870
You'll never figure it out anyway.

34:20.350 --> 34:21.230
Anyway,

34:21.420 --> 34:23.080
it's all because of your face.

34:23.540 --> 34:25.139
But I just can't accept it.

34:25.670 --> 34:26.670
You know, you're

34:27.060 --> 34:29.659
not gentle, not caring,
not even interesting.

34:29.699 --> 34:30.540
But why are those girls

34:30.540 --> 34:31.929
so eager to chase after you?

34:31.929 --> 34:33.139
Where do I fall short?

34:33.940 --> 34:35.770
Look at me from head to toe,
left to right,

34:35.770 --> 34:36.770
or from any angle.

34:36.770 --> 34:38.620
Am I not qualified to be
the campus heartthrob?

34:38.620 --> 34:39.820
Except for my height.

34:42.400 --> 34:43.460
I'm going out later

34:44.980 --> 34:45.909
to meet someone.

34:46.980 --> 34:47.750
If you're free,

34:47.750 --> 34:49.409
send her to Jin Qiang's place,

34:50.130 --> 34:51.260
campus heartthrob.

34:52.659 --> 34:53.790
Where are you going?

34:56.409 --> 34:57.810
You've made up your mind?

35:01.350 --> 35:02.060
Got it.

35:08.850 --> 35:10.140
Why would Jin Zhao

35:10.600 --> 35:12.600
buy that thing for me all of a sudden?

35:13.320 --> 35:14.470
What does he mean?

35:16.280 --> 35:18.510
Could it be that he needed it for himself

35:19.180 --> 35:19.980
but accidentally

35:19.980 --> 35:22.040
put it in the plastic bag meant for me?

35:22.580 --> 35:24.230
That must be it.

35:26.910 --> 35:28.570
Who does he want to use it with?

35:28.670 --> 35:29.310
But

35:29.680 --> 35:31.230
if he has a girlfriend,

35:31.720 --> 35:32.910
wouldn't it be

35:32.930 --> 35:34.450
awkward for me to be there?

35:35.100 --> 35:36.100
And I couldn't

35:36.120 --> 35:38.290
keep going there and disrupting his life.

35:38.290 --> 35:40.290
It'd be inappropriate
for even a real sister,

35:40.290 --> 35:41.290
let alone

35:42.530 --> 35:45.190
someone like me
who has no blood relation to him.

35:46.860 --> 35:48.390
That's my alma mater, look.

35:53.900 --> 35:55.700
You also studied at this school?

35:56.020 --> 35:56.830
Yes.

35:58.580 --> 35:59.580
You know what?

35:59.880 --> 36:02.360
When I was in school,

36:02.940 --> 36:04.500
I was quite the big shot.

36:04.910 --> 36:06.390
Countless girls came to our school

36:06.390 --> 36:07.990
just to catch a glimpse of me.

36:08.740 --> 36:09.810
With this hairstyle of mine,

36:09.810 --> 36:12.140
I was like Manshi's Takashi Kashiwabara,

36:12.310 --> 36:13.910
my high school's Shun Oguri.

36:17.100 --> 36:18.020
No exaggeration,

36:18.020 --> 36:18.960
during all 3 years of high school,

36:18.960 --> 36:20.960
I was the most handsome guy in the band.

36:20.960 --> 36:22.820
I was just one spot away from being

36:23.000 --> 36:24.800
the most handsome guy on campus.

36:25.290 --> 36:26.950
What do you mean by "one spot"?

36:27.460 --> 36:29.310
Well, after I registered,

36:29.500 --> 36:30.940
another guy came.

36:31.710 --> 36:33.500
He was taller than even the seniors

36:33.500 --> 36:35.360
and immediately
attracted everyone's attention.

36:35.360 --> 36:36.510
These girls started

36:36.690 --> 36:38.890
spreading the word and going to see him.

36:39.380 --> 36:40.190
This guy was

36:41.120 --> 36:41.910
Brandy.

36:44.400 --> 36:46.310
Let me tell you an interesting story.

36:46.310 --> 36:47.580
In high school, when most boys

36:47.580 --> 36:49.140
hadn't started growing taller yet,

36:49.140 --> 36:51.100
Brandy was already over 180 cm tall.

36:51.100 --> 36:52.870
During our school's cleaning days,

36:52.870 --> 36:53.620
for their class's cleaning,

36:53.620 --> 36:55.950
Brandy was always the one wiping windows.

36:56.100 --> 36:57.080
The most ridiculous part was

36:57.080 --> 36:59.460
that the class next door
would borrow him to wipe theirs.

36:59.460 --> 37:00.880
Whenever he went to wipe windows,

37:00.880 --> 37:01.880
many girls

37:02.230 --> 37:04.100
would poke their heads out to watch him.

37:04.100 --> 37:05.270
I didn't understand back then

37:05.270 --> 37:07.540
what was so interesting
about wiping windows.

37:07.540 --> 37:08.740
I only found out later

37:09.020 --> 37:10.350
that his uniform would ride up

37:10.350 --> 37:11.690
when he cleaned windows,

37:11.690 --> 37:13.220
so they could see his waist.

37:30.450 --> 37:32.230
What's so great
about seeing someone's waist?

37:32.230 --> 37:33.350
How would I know

37:33.350 --> 37:34.810
about your weird hobbies?

37:37.140 --> 37:37.780
By the way,

37:38.130 --> 37:39.770
Brandy asked me
to send you to Jin Qiang's place

37:39.770 --> 37:41.430
after this driving practice.

37:43.690 --> 37:44.610
Does Jin Zhao

37:45.150 --> 37:46.310
have a girlfriend?

37:48.100 --> 37:49.300
Well, how can I put it?

37:50.040 --> 37:51.640
Brandy hasn't confirmed it.

37:52.290 --> 37:53.820
So I shouldn't say too much.

37:54.350 --> 37:55.140
But I can give you

37:55.140 --> 37:56.870
a little insider information.

37:57.140 --> 37:58.190
Many years ago,

37:58.250 --> 38:00.400
I dragged Brandy to a night market.

38:00.910 --> 38:02.100
After browsing around,

38:02.100 --> 38:03.360
I didn't buy anything,

38:03.620 --> 38:05.080
but he bought an ornament.

38:05.100 --> 38:07.160
I think the answer to your question is

38:07.350 --> 38:08.680
right on that ornament.

38:09.310 --> 38:11.390
It should be attached
to a certain key, I think.

38:11.390 --> 38:12.460
If you have time,

38:12.670 --> 38:13.600
you can go find it

38:13.720 --> 38:14.850
and know the answer.

38:44.770 --> 38:45.540
The Association's points

38:45.540 --> 38:48.200
stack up
based on historical race performance.

38:49.260 --> 38:51.540
Outsiders can hardly
make it into the rankings.

38:51.540 --> 38:52.580
But M-night itself is already

38:52.580 --> 38:53.840
awash with top racers.

38:54.270 --> 38:56.060
To get into the top 10

38:56.610 --> 38:58.580
within six months is almost impossible.

38:58.580 --> 39:00.040
But only racers who make it

39:00.360 --> 39:02.490
to the top few spots with enough points

39:03.220 --> 39:04.890
will get noticed by the rest.

39:05.540 --> 39:06.390
I did my best.

39:06.750 --> 39:08.210
The car isn't good enough?

39:09.140 --> 39:10.650
It needs major modifications.

39:10.650 --> 39:12.050
There's not enough time.

39:12.940 --> 39:14.060
Are you giving up?

39:16.910 --> 39:18.240
I still have two months.

39:19.270 --> 39:20.530
I'm going to try again.

39:21.940 --> 39:23.630
When will you and your team
go back to China?

